** Heroku
- Download the Heroku Toolbelt
- Install and configure correct database gem
  - use 'pg' for production then $ bundle install --without production
- Create the application using $ heroku create
- Push the app $ git push heroku master
- Setup the database $ heroku run rails db:migrate

* Links
[Prevent Heroku from idling by pinging]
  (https://coderwall.com/p/u0x3nw/avoid-heroku-idling-with-new-relic-pings)

* Essential Commands
$ heroku run rails db:migrate
$ heroku run console
$ heroku logs -t
$ heroku restart
$ heroku config:set YOUR_VARIABLE=some_value
  # environment variables
$ heroku releases
$ heroku releases:rollback [version-number]
